definitions.definition: ( boxing , fencing , also often military ) Of an attack or offensive movement : directed toward a different part from the intended strike .

main_definition: ( boxing , fencing , also often military ) Of an attack or offensive movement : directed toward a different part from the intended strike .

definitions.definition: Of lines printed on paper as a handwriting guide : not bold ; faint , light ; also, of such paper: ruled with faint lines of this sort.

main_definition: Of lines printed on paper as a handwriting guide : not bold ; faint , light ; also, of such paper: ruled with faint lines of this sort. [from mid 19th c.]
